<ApiTester {endpoint}>

# Authenticate

Authenticate a wallet session with the RGS. Returns the player's current balance, any active round, game configuration including bet levels, and jurisdiction-specific settings.

<Callout type="warning">

This must be called before using other wallet endpoints. Otherwise, they will return `ERR_IS` (Invalid Session).

</Callout>

## Body Parameters

<ApiParamTable params={endpoint.params} />

## Response Fields

### `balance`

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `amount` | `integer` | Balance in minor currency units (e.g. 1000000000 = $1,000.00 for USD with 6 decimal places). |
| `currency` | `string` | ISO 4217 currency code. |

### `round`

Active round data if the player has an incomplete round. `null` if no round is in progress. The `round` returned may represent a currently active or the last completed round. Frontends should continue the round if it remains active.

<Callout type="info">

**Zero-payout rounds are auto-completed.** If the round resulted in zero winnings (payout = 0), the RGS automatically marks it as completed. You do **not** need to call [`/wallet/end-round`](/docs/api/end-round) for such rounds. Only rounds with a non-zero payout require an explicit end-round call.

</Callout>

### `config`

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `gameID` | `string` | The game identifier for this session. |
| `minBet` | `integer` | Minimum allowed bet in minor currency units. |
| `maxBet` | `integer` | Maximum allowed bet in minor currency units. |
| `stepBet` | `integer` | Bet increment step size. |
| `defaultBetLevel` | `integer` | Default bet level on session start. |
| `betLevels` | `integer[]` | All available bet levels. |
| `betModes` | `object` | Game-specific bet mode configuration. |
| `jurisdiction` | `object` | Jurisdiction-specific feature flags (see below). |

### `config.jurisdiction`

Do not used. Ignore.

### `meta`

Do not used. Ignore.

## Responses

<ApiResponseSection responses={endpoint.responses} />


</ApiTester>
